# Cybersecurity Home Lab

## Day 1

### Objective
Prepare my cybersecurity home lab.

### Completed
- Installed Oracle VM VirtualBox.
- Downloaded Windows Server 2022 Evaluation ISO.
- Downloaded Windows 11 ISO.
- Downloaded Kali Linux ISO.
- Organised ISO files into the CyberLab directory.

### Lessons Learned
I learned that ISO files are disk images used to install operating systems into virtual machines. They allow organisations to deploy servers and workstations without using physical installation media.

### Next Steps
Create my first virtual machine (TS-DC01) and install Windows Server 2022.

## Lesson Learned

I discovered that Windows was displaying my ISO files as "WinRAR archive (.iso)". Initially, I thought they needed to be extracted, but I learned that WinRAR was simply the default application associated with ISO files.

This reinforced the importance of checking the file extension rather than relying on the icon or application name before taking action.
